1. Importing use state
    a. import { useState } from 'react';

2. State behavior 
    a. if you put state on your function, it will change the value or whatever u set
    b. we are only going to refresh the specific part of the page, and we don't have to refresh the whole page

3. Implementing State
    a. first import it on the file import { useState } from 'react';
    b. put useState array inside the variable/function = const [count, setCount] = useState(0);